arch:property.oc:show_val: X3 is a fragment of a bone ring. Part came from flotation, separated by a modern break, so recorded here. F1 is a fragment of a different ring, from sample 3 >4 mm flotation. Last number = 1 {2002: Should have been a longer FUD; can we find it?) NR 2005: A little additional material has appeared. Ca. 10 mostly sheep-size fragments, about 30% burnt. No apparent gnawing, one digested. Diagnostics are sheep/goat. Moderate fragmentation, surface condition somewhat variable. Looks like fill. Last number = 111

arch:string.div: The unique identifier for each contextual unit, matching those used in the central Çatalhöyük excavation database and in publications. The excavation uses single-context recording.
